<center><h1> Situation Metaphor (Contd) </h1>

<h2><u> Situation Space</u> </h2></center>
<h2>
The Organisation of Situation space is hierarchical.
It  consists of following 3 categories from Top to Bottom levels. 

<ul>
<li>Abstract Situation </li>
<li>Instance Situation </li>
<li>Basic Situation </li>
</ul>

<u>Abstract Situation </u>

       This situation describes a particular category of User's goals and
       is not necessary to refer to a particular location or timeinterval.

       <u>Ex:</u> Sales of Product A 



<u>Instance situation </u>

       This situation describes the occurences of the Abstract situations
       with actual attribute values.

       <u>Ex:</u> Sale of Product A to Lawson shops



<u> Basic Situation </u>

        This  situation describes the actual occurances of instances
        situations in the real world. They have actual values of location,
        time and activities

        <u>Ex:</u> The product A is delivered to Lawson shop on Hirodaimae
        street at 9:21 on December 1, 1999.






